profile_description:Rwanda Biwumba NOUA Red Bourbon Natural\vGrape Jasmine | Altitude: 1800-2000m\vMoisture: 11.6% | Density: 817g/L\vLoad: 120g\v\vVersion 1 - Based on Kaffelogic official F-NAT 1500-2200\v(SeanBrews v2.5) as primary template.\v\vAdjustments from official template:\v- Preheat 850->820W (817g/L medium density, fresh bean\v  11.6% moisture, natural process needs gentler start)\v- expect_fc 206->202C (1800-2000m mid-range, 817g/L\v  medium density, est. FC ~198-203C)\v- expect_colrchange set to 165C (natural process,\v  slightly earlier than washed)\v- Kd 3.55->3.10 (proven stable from Catimor V3-V5)\v- Cooldown 17000/16000/85C (light roast fast lock)\v- Roast levels shifted down for light-medium target\v- min_ROR kept at 0.2 (template value, safe)\v\vRoast profile and fan profile kept from official\vF-NAT 1500-2200 template (6-point curve). No Zone.\vSchema 1.4.\v\vExpected FC: ~198-203C\v\vRecommended Levels:\v\vLight Filter: Level 1.5 (~205C, ~14% dev)\vLight Balanced: Level 2.0 (~207C, ~16% dev) <- Target\vMedium Light: Level 2.5 (~209C, ~18% dev)\vMedium: Level 3.0 (~211C, ~20% dev)\v\vNatural process note: high sugar content,\vmonitor for scorching in early phase.\vExpect wine/dried fruit/apricot/orange notes.\v\vC40 pour-over grind: 22-26 clicks\vResting period: 7-14 days\v
